uieting pattern in the legal and literary representations of women and provides a new recognition of the significance of sexuality and gender in the way we narrate our world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aEnglish fictionxHistory and criticism. 0aLaw and literaturezEnglandxHistory. 0aLaw in literature. 0aWomen and literaturezEnglandxHistory. 0aWomen in literature. 0aWomenxLegal status, laws, etc.zEnglandxHistory. 7aLAW / Gender & the Law.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804773683zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804773683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804773683.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles